  "prompt": "What universities does Immune Design recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Immune Design, like many companies in the biotechnology and pharmaceutical sectors, typically recruits new graduates from a range of universities, particularly those with strong programs in life sciences, biotechnology, and related fields. They often look for candidates from universities known for their research and innovation in these areas.\n\nIn terms of majors, Immune Design and similar companies are usually interested in candidates with degrees in:\n\n- Molecular Biology\n- Immunology\n- Biochemistry\n- Biotechnology\n- Bioengineering\n- Microbiology\n- Genetics\n- Pharmacology\n- Biomedical Engineering\n- Pharmaceutical Sciences\n\nSpecific recruitment patterns can change over time, so it's a good idea for prospective candidates to check the company\u2019s careers page or reach out directly to their HR department for the most current information. Additionally, networking through alumni connections or attending industry-related job fairs can provide insight into recruitment practices.",
